            <Label TextColor="Black" HorizontalOptions="Center" Text="Our journey began in 1986 and since then there has been no looking back. The institution remains committed to being a premier institution of the locality. Our resolve is unparalleled, our efforts unrelenting and our vision truly progressive. Divisional Public School and College Sahiwal was established in 1986 under the aegis of Sahiwal Educational Trust in a rented building in Farid Town. It was shifted to its present capacious premises stretching over 68 acres on 27th Ramadan 1407 Haijri, the 25th May 1987. Mian Muhammad Nawaz Sharif, the then Chief Minister Punjab inaugurated the present Senior School Block on 15th September 1988. Science Block was added in 1991. Junior School building was constructed in 1994. Girls School was established in 1997. School Mosque was constructed in 1998. D.P.S. was upgraded as Inter College in year 2000. Since its establishment, the school has been producing excellent results and has proved itself a quality institution. D.P.S. has now become the first choice of the parents." FontSize="18" />
